LAGOS  – The Nigeria Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA) over the weekend marked the agency’s Corporate Dinner and Merit Awards tagged ‘ A Night With Maritime Stars’, where Constance Omagbemi emerged NIMASA employee of the year carting Awae a cheque of N1 million and automatic promotion to the next position. Also TOTAL E&PB bagged the best offshore company award for its compliance to the International Ships and Ports Security (ISPS) Offshore Facility for 2019, while the most compliant ISPS Onshore Facility for 2019 went to APMT. Tincan Island Container Terminals was awarded the best Terminal / Jetty operator, while Maritime Academy of Nigeria (MAN), Oron in Akwa Ibom State was given the best Maritime Training Institution for 2019. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The award for the best shipping company in terms of marine environment management went to West African Ventures, while the best Cabotage operator for year 2019 was given to Awarise. The award for the company with the largest combined tonnage went to the Sea Navigation International Limited, while the overall Shipping Company of the year 2019 award went to GAC Shipping Limited.